# ====================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Update your .env file with the CORRECT Supabase connection
# ====================================================================

To fix the authentication error:

1. Go to: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/tfzggfbozmqqedrfprsj/settings/database

2. Find the "Connection string" section

3. Choose "Session mode" (Transaction mode for connection pooling)

4. Copy the connection string - it should look like:
   postgresql://postgres.tfzggfbozmqqedrfprsj:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-us-west-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true

5. Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your actual database password

6. Update the DATABASE_URL in your .env file with this string

IMPORTANT: Do NOT include the square brackets [] - they are just placeholders!

Example of CORRECT format:
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.tfzggfbozmqqedrfprsj:MyActualPassword123@aws-0-us-west-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"

After updating:
1. Stop the dev server (Ctrl+C)
2. Run: npx prisma generate
3. Run: npx prisma db push
4. Run: npm run db:seed
5. Run: npm run dev
